profile_positions.description:
As overall manager of the Maximazing ART for Better Health and Zero New HIV Infections (MaxART) programme in Swaziland/Eswatini, I was responsible for: 
* Global programme and grant management of the groundbreaking MaxART programme in Eswatini (12.7 million Euro, funded through the Dutch Postcode Lottery Dream Fund and Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands);
* Building and strengthening the multidisciplinary and multicultural consortium with Eswatini government, international and local NGOs, networks of people living with HIV and research institutions;
* Capacity building of community based partners, and ensuring linkage of health and community system elements of the programme;
* Facilitate knowledge exchange, documentation and sharing programme results and lessons learned in regional and international networks and conferences;
* Secretariat for the MaxART Steering Committee  (CEO level) and International Advisory Board (high profile HIV and research experts).

MaxART included a unique package of interventions aimed at strengthening health and community systems to improve the health of the people of Swaziland/Eswatini and  focused on a dramatically scale-up of HIV testing, treatment and retention in care, and to provide proof that offering all people living with HIV with early treatment improves clinical outcomes, and is feasible, acceptable, affordable in Eswatini’s government­ managed health system.
